==English==
===Etymology===
French [[lanturlu]], originally the refrain of a sixteenth-century song.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /læntə'lu:/

===Noun===
'''lanterloo'''
# a meaningless [[chant]] or [[refrain]]
#:*'''1963''': The helmsman began to sing a monotonous, Levantine '''lanterloo'''. — Thomas Pynchon, ''V.''